{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The review input is scoped to the lines that changed, not the full content of each modified file.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure appears at a local module handoff (diff parser/file-loader -> review-input builder). A unit test of only one function can miss wiring mistakes (e.g., correct parser output but wrong field passed downstream). No real OS/network/subprocess is required, and correctness does not depend on model output quality.","test_description":"Run an in-process test that wires real diff-ingestion and input-construction modules together using a fixture PR diff with unchanged file regions. Assert the produced review payload includes only changed hunks/line ranges and excludes unchanged content.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Inline comments are attached to the correct positions in the diff view on the pull request.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This is about real PR diff-position semantics and API behavior. Mocks often hide off-by-one/path/commit-sha/position-field mismatches that only fail against the real GitHub endpoint and real diff view mapping.","test_description":"Against a real test PR, submit inline comments using computed positions and verify they appear on the intended lines in the PR diff UI/API response (path, side, line/position).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.88,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The agent identifies at least one real defect in a pull request that contains a known introduced bug.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real model judgment (defect detection quality), which a stub cannot validate. Behavior text is explicitly about identifying a real defect,